22/06/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- In a press statement released Monday (21 June), the European Parliament's rapporteur for Romania praised the government's decision to "crack down on child trafficking". Baroness Emma Nicholson stressed that the results of the "strong policies" adopted by the government are already evident.
Also Monday, European Commissioner for Enlargement Guenter Verheugen visited Romania. Just days ago, Brussels reaffirmed 2007 as the official accession date for both Romania and Bulgaria. (Rompres - 22/06/04; Mediafax - 21/06/04)
